---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---

<Base
  title="Privacy Policy — Animate Stock"
  description="Privacy policy for the Animate Stock iPhone app and animatestock.com."
  path="/privacy"
>
  <article class="prose">
    <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
    <p><em>Last updated: June 10, 2026</em></p>
    <p>
      This policy describes how Animate Stock (the iOS app) and animatestock.com
      (the website), operated by Applorium, handle your information.
    </p>

    <h2>What the app collects</h2>
    <p>
      Animate Stock does not require an account and does not collect personal
      information. Your projects, custom events, and exported videos are stored
      locally on your device.
    </p>

    <h2>Market data requests</h2>
    <p>
      When you search for a ticker or load price history, the app requests data
      from third-party market data providers. These requests include the ticker
      symbol and date range but no personal identifiers beyond what any internet
      request technically includes (such as your IP address, handled by the
      provider under their own policies).
    </p>

    <h2>Photos access</h2>
    <p>
      If you choose to save an exported video or GIF, the app asks for
      permission to add it to your photo library. The app only writes the files
      you export; it does not read your existing photos.
    </p>

    <h2>The website</h2>
    <p>
      animatestock.com is a static website. It does not set cookies and does not
      run third-party trackers.
    </p>

    <h2>Changes</h2>
    <p>
      If this policy changes, the updated version will be posted on this page
      with a new "last updated" date.
    </p>

    <h2>Contact</h2>
    <p>
      Questions? Email <a href="mailto:apps@applorium.com">apps@applorium.com</a>.
    </p>
  </article>
</Base>
